      <debateSection>
        <heading>TABLING REPORTS, REGULATIONS AND OTHER PAPERS</heading>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : The honourable Minister of Justice.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#4fe6044a-d86e-4a24-bc37-127add6fe273">
          <from>HON. ROSS LANDRY</from>
          <p>HON. ROSS LANDRY : Mr. Speaker, I would like to present The Nova Scotia Freedom of Information and Protection of Privacy Review Office, 2011 Annual Report.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : The report is tabled.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#0768c045-71ae-4890-b6be-c52eb783ee95">
          <from>HON. DARRELL DEXTER</from>
          <p>HON. DARRELL DEXTER : Mr. Speaker, it's my pleasure to introduce to the House of Assembly today Lee and Shannon Ferrier from Toronto who are in your gallery. Lee Ferrier is a retired Superior Court Justice for the Province of Ontario and is serving on the Pension Appeals Board which is taking place in Halifax this week.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : We welcome all our guests to the gallery and hope they enjoy this afternoon's proceedings.</p>
        </speech>
      </debateSection>
      <debateSection>
        <heading>STATEMENTS BY MINISTERS</heading>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : The honourable Premier.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#0768c045-71ae-4890-b6be-c52eb783ee95">
          <from>THE PREMIER</from>
          <p>THE PREMIER : Mr. Speaker, I rise in my place today to talk about one of the deadliest mining disasters in this country's history, a tragic event that resulted in an improved approach to the protection of Nova Scotia's health and safety and greater awareness of safety issues. The Westray mining disaster is a tragedy that continues to haunt workers and their families in the community of Plymouth, throughout Pictou County and right across Nova Scotia and, in fact, this country.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : The honourable Leader of the Official Opposition.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#3d2afb09-46bb-45b0-8cdb-90ba97b15ed0">
          <from>HON. STEPHEN MCNEIL</from>
          <p>HON. STEPHEN MCNEIL : Thank you, Mr. Speaker, and I want to thank the Premier for an advance copy of his remarks. I think all members of the House want to associate ourselves with his remarks today.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : The honourable Leader of the Progressive Conservative Party.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#adf62df0-6616-4824-87bd-59fd0bc41914">
          <from>HON. JAMIE BAILLIE</from>
          <p>HON. JAMIE BAILLIE : Mr. Speaker, thank you to the Premier for a copy of his statement. Today I rise in my place and join my fellow Nova Scotians as we remember the 20th Anniversary of the Westray mine disaster.</p>
        </speech>
        <speech by="#75109949-5b99-4b9c-b9fd-d85a8ce227ab">
          <from>MR. SPEAKER</from>
          <p>MR. SPEAKER : I would ask all members now to stand for a moment of silence.</p>
        </speech>
        <narrative>
          <p>A moment of silence was observed.</p>
        </narrative>
